Problem: Subarray Sum Equals K
Topic: Arrays, Prefix Sum
Difficulty: Medium
Approach:
Use a nested loop to consider all subarrays. For each starting index, keep adding elements and check if the sum equals k. Increment count whenever the sum matches k.
Time Complexity: O(n²)
Space Complexity: O(1)

Code:
class Solution {
public:
         int subarraySum(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
         int count = 0;
         int n=nums.size();
         int i,j;
         for(i=0;i<n;i++){
            int new_sum=0;
         for(j=i;j<n;j++){
            new_sum+=nums[j];

            if(new_sum==k){
                count++;
            }
         }
         }
       return count;
         }
};
